.TH simple_shell 1 "January 2025" "1.1" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command-line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RB [ no options ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple UNIX command-line interpreter written in C. It supports the execution of basic commands along with their arguments. This shell reads input from the user, parses the input into a command and arguments, and executes the command.

.SH USAGE
After starting the shell, you will see a
.B $
prompt. You can type a command followed by its arguments and press Enter. The shell will execute the command and display the prompt again. To exit the shell, use the
.B exit
command or press Ctrl+D.

.SH COMMANDS
The shell can execute any binary that exists in the current directory or by providing the absolute path.

Example usage:
.TP
\fBls -l\fP
Lists files in the current directory in long format.

.TP
\fBecho "Hello, World!"\fP
Displays the text "Hello, World!" on the screen.

.TP
\fBexit\fP
Exits the shell.

.SH OPTIONS
.B simple_shell
does not support any options.

.SH FILES
.B simple_shell
requires access to standard UNIX executables.

.SH AUTHOR
Diego Mercado <mercadodiego2006gmail.com>
